www
.colour fulnuuk.comILISIMASARIAQARTUT...
VÆRD AT VIDE...
GOOD TO KNOW...
SIUARIARTORTITSINERMI INGERLATSISOQ: Takornariaqarnermik
suliaqarfi mmi kaaviiaartit koruunit milliardip aff aanut anngukkiartuaalersimasinnaapput.
Suliaqarfi mmi suliffi ssat 700-t missaanniittut maanna pilersinneqarsimalerput. Sulilu
amerlanerit pilersinneqartussanngorunarput: – Kalaallit Nunaanni takornariaqarnerup
ukiuni makkunani annertusiartuinnarnera ersarilluinnarpoq. Kalaallit Nunaanni angala-
titsisartut, ukiarmi Vestnorden Travel Martimut peqataasut, nioqqutissiamik soqutigi-
neqarluarnerannik misigisaqarsimapput. Taamaattumik Kalaallit Nunaanni nunarsuarmi
nittarsaassineq ukiuni aggersuni ingerlateqqinniarparput, Visit Greenlandip pisortaa Julia
Pars oqarpoq. (Najoqqutaq: Sermitsiaq)
VÆKSTMOTOR: Omsætningen i turistbranchen kan være på vej mod den halve milli-
ard kroner. Der er nu skabt cirka 700 jobs i branchen. Og fl ere kan være på vej: – Det er helt
tydeligt, at turismen i Grønland vokser i disse år. De grønlandske operatører, som deltog i
efterårets Vestnorden Messe, har oplevet stor interesse for deres produkter. Vi vil derfor de
kommende år fortsætte arbejdet med at markedsføre Grønland på den internationale scene,
siger Julia Pars, direktør i Visit Greenland. (Kilde: Sermitsiaq)
GROWTH GENERATOR: Revenue in the tourist industry could be nearing half a
billion kroner. There are now 700 jobs in the industry and more could be on the way. These
years, tourism in Greenland is clearly expanding. The Greenlandic operators who took part
in the autumn’s Vestnorden Travel Mart have experienced great interest in their products.
– In coming years, we will therefore continue to work at promoting Greenland on the
international scene, says Julia Pars, director of Visit Greenland. (Source: Sermitsiaq)
[KAL] Hotel Arctic immini ornigassaqqissutut
kajungernassuseqartorujussuuvoq.
[DK] Hotel Arctic er en magnet i sig selv.
[GB] Hotel Arctic is an attraction in itself.
SINERISSAP SAPANGAA: Ilulissani takor-
nariaqarneq siuariartortuarsinnarpoq. Kisitsinermit
takutinneqarpoq illoqarfi mmi unnuisarfi it maanna
20-nit amerlanerulersimasut, AirBnB-t amerliar-
tuinnartut ilanngullugit. Niuerfi mmut siunnersorti
Mads Lumholt Visit Greenlandimeersoq naapertor-
lugu, Ilulissat Kalaallit Nunaanni sulinngiff eqarfi ttut
malunnaateqarnerpaajuvoq: Hotel Arctic kajungi-
nerineqarnerpaasartut ilaattut oqaatigineqarpoq.
(Najoqqutaq: Sermitsiaq)
THE GEM OF THE COAST: Tourism
continues to boom in Ilulissat. Figures show that
there are now more that 20 places to spend the
night in the town, including an increasing number
of AirBnBs. According to marketing consultant
Mads Lumholt from Visit Greenland, Ilulissat is the
biggest leisure market in Greenland: Hotel Arctic is
named as being one of the major attractions.
(Source: Sermitsiaq)
76
KYSTENS PERNE: Turismen fortsætter med
at boome i Ilulissat. En optælling viser, at der nu
er fl ere end 20 overnatningssteder i byen, inklusiv
et stigende antal AirBnB. Ifølge markedskonsulent
Mads Lumholt fra Visit Greenland er Ilulisat det
mest leisure-prægede marked i Grønland: Hotel
Arctic nævnes som en af de store magneter.
(Kilde: Sermitsiaq)
[KAL] Takornariat suli amerlanerit tikittalerput.
[DK] Flere turister på vej.
[GB] More tourists are on the way.
Suluk nr. 1 | Air Greenland | Infl ight Magazine 2020Mittarfeqarfinniinnera nuannaraara
USSASSAARUT/ANNONCE
Randy A. Hansen, 24-nik ukiulik, Mittarfeqarfinni qulimiguullit mittarfianni assistentiunini nuannarigaluarlugu al-
laffimmiutut ilinniagaqarusuppoq. Ulloq 1. aggusti Timmisartunik Sullissinermut Immikkoortortaqarfimmi allaffim-
miutut ilinniartunngorpoq.
Qaqortumi qulimiguullit mittarfianni assistentitut pissanganartu­
mik atorfik Mittarfeqarfiit Nuummi qullersaqarfianni Timmisartunik
Sullissinermut Immikkoortortaqarfimmi allaffimmiutut ilinniartuu­
nermik taarserneqarpoq. Randy­immi Niuernermik Ilinniarfimmi al­
laffimmiutut ilinniakkani naammassiguniuk Mittarfeqarfinniiginnar­
nissani takorloorpaa.
­ Mittarfeqarfinni sulinera assut nuannaraara, allaffimmiutulli ilinnia­
gaqarnissamik kissaateqarpunga. Ilinniartutut Mittarfeqarfinniigin­
narsinnaagama taamaammat nuannaarutigeqaara, Randy oqarpoq.
Randy Timmisartunik Sullissinermut Immikkoortortaqarfimmi al­
laffimmiutut ilinniartunngortinneqarpoq qulimiguullit mittarfian­
ni suliassanik isumaginninnermut misilittagaqarnera pissutigalugu.
Timmisartunik Sullissinermut Immikkoortortaqarfimmi suluusalin­
nut mittarfinni qulimiguulinnullu mittarfinni suliassarpassuit isu­
mannaatsumik sukkasuumillu qanoq suliarineqartarnissaannik peri­
utsit ilaatigut suliarineqarput.
­ Qulimiguulinnut mittarfimmi ulloq qanoq ingerlasartoq nalunngila­
ra. Nassatalerinermiit, ilaasunik isumaginninnermut, orsersuinermiil­
lu mittarfimmi qulimiguulimmik nalinginnaasumik sullissinermut.
Taamaalillunga Timmisartunik Sullissinermut Aqutsisup immikkoor­
tortaqarfimmi suliassaanik isumaginninnerani tunioraaqataasinnaa­
vunga. Suleqatigiilluaqaagut, Randy nuannaarluni oqaluttuarpoq.
Randy­ip ilinniakkani aasakkut 2020­mi naammassissavaa.
Siunissami qanoq ikkumaarnera suli ilisimanngilaa Qaqortumulli
angerlarumaarnissani kissaatigalugu.
­ Ilinniagara naammassigukku Mittarfeqarfinniiginnarsinnaanngik­
kuma aqqutinni misilittakkat suli amerlanerusut suut aqqusaarumaar­
nerlugit takujumaarpara. Neriuutiginerpaavarali Mittarfeqarfinni siu­
nissaqarumaarlunga assersuutigalugu Qaqortumi mittarfittaassaq
atulerpat.
Mittarfeqarfiit ilinniarfeqarfittut
Mittarfeqarfiit Kalaallit Nunaanni ilinniarfiit annerpaat ilagaat.
Ilinniakkanit arlalippassuarnit suliffimmi sungiusartut saniatigut
Mittarfeqarfiit namminneq ilinniarfeqarput, taakkulu mittarfinni
najukkami immikkut ilisimasalinnik ilinniagaqartitsiuarnissamik
qularnaarisuupput.
Mittarfeqarfiit assigiinngitsunik 19­inik ilinniarfigineqarsinnaa­
voq, agguaqatigiissillugillu suliffeqarfimmi sulisut 35­t ilinniak­
kamik ingerlassaqartarput. Mittarfeqarfiit siunissami eqqortunik
sulisartoqarnissaat inuiaqatigiillu tamarmiusut ilinniarsimas­
sutsikkut qaffassarnissaat qularnaarniarlugit ilinniartitaaneq pi­
ngaartinneqarpoq.
I am happy to work at Mittarfeqarfiit
24-year old Randy A. Hansen was happy to work as heliport assistant i Mittarfeqarfiit but
wanted to be trained as office assistant. As of August 1st, she started as office trainee in
Ground Handling.
­ I was really happy about my
job in Mittarfeqarfiit, but I had
a desire to get training as of­
fice assistant. So I was really
pleased that I was allowed to
continue as a trainee.
Randy became a student in the Ground Handling section because of
her experience in handling the tasks of a helicopter airfield. Among
other things, the Ground Handling section works with procedures on
how to solve the many tasks in an airport and helicopter airfield, sa
sa­
fely and efficiently.
­ I know the daily routines at a helicopter airfield. Everything from
handling luggage and passengers, to refueling and service in general
of a helicopter on the ground. That way I can spar with the Ground
Handling Manager in the execution of the section’s tasks. We have a
really good collaboration, says a happy Randy.
In the summer of 2020, Randy will finish her training. She does not
yet know what the future will offer, as she has a desire to return to
her hometown of Qaqortoq.
­ Unless I can continue in Mittarfeqarfiit after my graduation, I have
to develop new experiences and see what I will meet on my way. But I
sincerely hope that I can have a future in Mittarfeqarfiit in Qaqortoq,
for example when the new airport comes into operation.
Mittarfeqarfiit as an educational institution
Mittarfeqarfiit is one of Greenland’s largest educational institu­
tions. In addition to having trainees from a wide range of pro­
grams, Mittarfeqarfiit has its own training programs, which en­
sure that local specialists are continuously trained for the air­
ports.
Today, there are 19 different programs, and on an average day,
there are 35 employees in training in the company. Mittarfeqarfiit
is committed to educate our staff to ensure that Mittarfeqarfiit
has the right manpower in the future, and to raise the educational
level of the entire community.
An exciting job as a heliport assistant
at the helicopter airfield in Qaqortoq
has been replaced with a student seat in
the Ground Handling section at Mittarfe­
qarfiit’s headquarters in Nuuk. Ran­
dy has a dream to continue wor­
king in Mittarfeqarfiit when she
finishes her office training at Ni­
uernermik IlinniarfikQanormi taava ippa...
Aviâja Egede
Lyngeulluni
Meeqqat illersuisuat
Ulloq aallartittarpara...kigaatsumik eqeeriartorlunga tiitorujoor-
lunga. Qimmeq aamma sammineqartarpoq, tamatigut iternissara
utaqqisarpaa. Meeraallunga sunngornissannik takorloortarsimavara....qanganisar-
siortunngornissara, nunarsuarmi kulturinut assigiinngitsunut
angalallunga.
Qaaqqusat sunik nerisassiuuttarpigit?
Nunatta pissarititaannik, qangatut nutaaliaralugillu. Nillataarsitsivinni peqqinnarnerpaaq peqqinnangninnerpaarlu tassaap-
put ...spinati qalipallu.
Atisat qalipaatigissut qernertulluunniit?
Marluutillugit. Arlaannut utoqqatserusuppit?
Erngerlunga imaluunniit pisup kingunitsiaa utoqqatsertarpunga
allat ajuallatsikkusunnginnakkit. Taamaattumik naamik, utoqqat-
serfigisassat utoqqatserfigineqareerput.
Peqqinnissaq pingaartippiuk?
Assut.
Kiattumiinneq nillertumiinnerluunniit?
Taakku akornanni.
Avatangiisinut siunnersuutissaqarpit?
Atoqqiineq.
78
Nerisassiorneq igariikkalluunniit?
Annermik iganerusarpunga.
Angerlarsimaffiit qanoq pequsersorsimaviuk?
Inuunermi aqqusaakkannut eqqaassutissanik annikitsunik pisari-
itsunillu. Panimma mikisuullinili qalipagai iikkanniinnerupput.
Suluk nr. 1
Inflight Magazine 2020
ALLATTOQ: Jette AndersenAkisoorsuarnik soqutigisaqanngilanga, oqartariaqarpungali
anger­larsimaffiga aalajangersimasumik isikkoqanngimmat.
Ajunngilarli naleqartitakka pigisani tigussaasuniinngimmata.
Suna piisaarutiginerpaasarpiuk?
Ajornakusoorpoq. Isumaqarpunga peqqissuunera soqutigilluin-
nakkannillu sulinera piisaarnerusoq.
Illoqarfigisat sutigut immikkut ittuua?
Inuit taama amerlatigisut assigiinngisitaartuummata pissanga-
narlutillu. Amerlaqisut ilisarisimanerulerusukkaluarpakka.
Nunarsuarmi ajornartorsiutit annersaat massakkorpiaq sunaava?
Inuit atukkamikkut nikinganerujussuat.
Imeq sodavandiluunniit?
Imeq puaasalik, sukkoqanngitsoq.
Asanninneq qanoq misigisimanarpa?
Asanninneq toqqissisimanarpoq, inissaqartitsilluni aqajannguum-
mernarlunilu
Pisimasup suup inuttut ineriartortissimavaatit?
Amerlaqaat, ataatsiinnaanngitsullu kinaatsutsikkut sunnersima-
vaanga. Pisut nuannersut nuanniinnerillu. Nalinginnaasumilli
inuusuttuullunga angalasimanera nunarsuarmilu angalaarnera,
ilusilersuisimaqaat.
Inuuninni ...unneqqarissuseq naapertuuttuunerlu pinngitsoorsin-
naanngilakka.
Annilaanganartittarpara ... angallannermi atugassat ilaat annilaa­
nganartitakka.
Suluk nr. 1 | Air Greenland | Inflight Magazine 2020
79[KAL] Aviâja Egede Lynge igarusunnerusarpoq
igariikkanik pisinermiit. Aamma ajunngilaq
igaat nammineq pisarisimagaanni.
[DK] Aviâja Egede Lynge vil helst lave mad, fremfor at
købe det udefra. Og så gør det ikke noget, at maden
er fanget selv.
[GB] Aviâja Egede Lynge prefers home-cooking over
take-out. And it is a bonus when it is something she
has caught herself.
Hvordan er det egentlig at være...
Aviâja
Egede Lynge
Børnetalsmand
TEKST: Jette Andersen
Hvad slags mad laver du til gæster?
Mad lavet af grønlandske råvarer, både traditionelt og internationalt in-
spireret.
Farverigt eller sort tøj?
Begge.
Går du op i sundhed?
Meget.
Varme eller kølige temperaturer?
Midt i mellem.
Har du et miljøtip?
Genbrug.
Mit drømmejob som barn var... arkæolog og rejse til alverdens forskellige
kulturer.
Det sundeste og mest usunde i mit køleskab er... spinat og fløde.
Er der nogle, du har lyst til at sige undskyld til?
Jeg siger altid undskyld med det samme eller indenfor en kort tid, da jeg
ikke kan lide at såre andre. Så nej, dem, der skal have en undskyldning, har
allerede fået den.
Madlavning eller købemad?
Laver altid helst mad.
Hvordan har du indrettet dit hjem?
Sparsomt og praktisk med gode minder fra livets vej. Min datters malerier
fra hun var lille til nu, ses mest på mine vægge. Jeg er ikke til store dyre
ting, og jeg må indrømme, at jeg ikke har særlig meget stil i hjemmet. Men
det gør ikke noget, da mine værdier ikke ligger i materielle ting.
Hvad er din største luksus?
Den er svær. Jeg synes, det er luksus, at jeg er rask og laver det, som jeg
brænder for.
Hvad gør din by til noget ganske særligt?
At der er så mange forskellige og spændende slags mennesker. Der er
mange, som jeg godt kunne tænke mig, at lære bedre at kende endnu.
Hvad er det største problem i verden lige nu?
Den store ulighed i livsvilkår for menneskene.
Jeg bliver nervøs over... nogle former for transportmidler, som kan give mig
angst.
Vand eller sodavand?
Vand med brus, uden sukker.
Hvordan føles kærlighed?
Kærlighed er tryg, rummelig, og giver bobler i maven.
Hvilken begivenhed har formet dig som menneske?
Rigtig mange begivenheder, og ikke kun én, har formet mig til den jeg er.
Både de gode og de mindre gode begivenheder. Men generelt har mine
rejser og ophold ude i verden i en ung alder, formet mig rigtig meget.
Jeg kan ikke leve uden... ærlighed og retfærdighed.
80
Suluk nr. 1
Inflight Magazine 2020
Jeg begynder min morgen med... at vågne langsomt og drikke en kop te.
Hunden får også opmærksomhed, han venter altid på at jeg vågner.What is it like to be...?
Aviâja
Egede Lynge
Children’s spokesman
TEXT: Jette Andersen
I start my morning by ... waking up slowly and drinking a cup of tea.
I give my dog, which is always waiting for me to wake up, some at-
tention.
What kind of food do you serve for your guests?
Food made with Greenlandic ingredients, with both traditional and
international inspiration.
Colourful or black clothes?
Both.
Are you interested in your health?
Very.
Home cooking or take-out?
I always prefer to cook.
The most healthy and unhealthy things in my refrigerator are ... spinach
and cream.
What is the interior design of your home like?
Spartan and practical with good memories from my journey through
life. My walls are mostly decorated with my daughter’s paintings
from when she was little and up to the present. I am not fond of big
expensive things and I have to admit that my home does not have
much style. But it doesn’t matter, since my values do not lie in mate-
rial things.
What is your greatest luxury?
That is a hard one. Luxury for me is when I am healthy and can do
what I am passionate about.
What makes your town special?
That there are so many different and interesting people. I would like
to get to know a lot of these people even better.
What is the biggest problem in the world right now?
The huge inequality in people’s living conditions.
I get nervous ...on some kinds of transport; they can make me anxious.
Warm or cool temperatures?
In between.
Do you have a tip for the environment?
Recycle.
When I was a child, my dream job was... to be an archaeologist, travel-
ling to different cultures around the world.
Is there anyone you would like to apologize to?
I always apologize at once or within a short time, because I do not
like to hurt others. So no, anyone who needed an apology has already
received one.
Water or soda?
Non-carbonated water without sugar.
What does love feel like?
Love is secure, gives space and it bubbles in your tummy.
Which event has formed you as a person?
There have been many events, not just one, that have made me who
I am; both good and less good events. But generally, my travels and
visits around the world at a young age did a lot to form me.
I cannot live without...honesty and fairness.Eqqumiitsuliortoq
misikkarissoq
Kalaallit Nunaata
eqqumiitsuliornikkut
oqaluttuassartaata ilaa
angerlaanneqarpoq
G
itz-Johansenip eqqumiitsuliaanik sisamanik katersu­
gaatinut pisinikkut eqqumiitsulianut katersugaasiv-
immut Nuuk Kuntsmuseumimut takorluukkat piviu­
sunngortinneqarput. Nutaatut pissarsiarineqartut
pisinnaanngorsimapput Ny Carlsbergfondimit tunissuteqarto-
qarneratigut. Pappiaramut eqqumiitsuliat pingasut uuliamillu
qalipagaq ataaseq pineqarput.
– Eqqumiitsulianit taakkunannga sisamanit Gitz-Johansenip
ilisarnarluartumik pinnguarpalaartumik, ajornanngitsumik
titartaariaasia Kalaallit Nunaannilu kulturimut misikkarissuse-
qarluartumik isiginnittaasia takutinneqarput, katersugaasiviup
aqutsisua Nivi Christensen oqarpoq.
– Eqqumiitsuliat eqqumiitsuliortut Danmarkimit aallartitaasi-
masut assigiinngitsut Kalaallit Nunaannik qanoq assigiinngitsi-
gisumik isiginnittaaseqarsimanerannik takutitseqataassapput.
Emanuel A. Petersen, Jette Bang aamma Gitz-Johansen tamarmik
ukiut 1930-kkut missaanni Kalaallit Nunaanniissimapput. Pe-
tersen pinngortitamik pingaartitsinerusimavoq, inuillu eqqumiit­
suliaani annikitsuinnarmik atuuffeqarsimallutik. Eqqumiitsu­
liaani seqerngup tarrilerneri qalipaatigissaartut nunamilu
kusanartumi qimussimik angalanerit pingaarnerpaasimapput.
Eqqumiitsuliai amerlanertigut isorartussutsinik annertuunik ta-
kutitsisumik qalipanneqartarsimapput. Gitz-Johansen kulturimik
ersersitsisarsimavoq, tamatumanilu arnat allaliunneqarsimasullu
qanimut misigissuseqarluartumillu sammisarsimallugit, Nivi
Christensen itisiliivoq.
Eskimo toqusoq
Katersugaasiviup aqutsisua naapertorlugu eqqumiitsuliat taakkua
sisamat – katersugaasivimmilu eqqumiitsuliat nunanit allaneersut
piffissamit tassannga pisut allat ilaat – Kalaallit Nunaata nuna-
siaataanerup nalaani qanoq isigineqarneranik ersersitsipput.
– Uuliamik qalipagarujussuaq »Eskimo toquvoq« Gitz-
Johansenimit ineriartornermut Kalaallit Nunaanni G50 aamma
G60 aqqutigalugit aallartinneqartumut toqqaannartumik
oqaaseqaataavoq. Kalaallit Nunaata nutarteriffigineqarneranik
naammaginninnginnnini akuttunngitsumik ersersittarsimavaa,
isumaqarami eskimuut kulturiannik aserorterinerusoq. Nutar-
terinerup aallartinneqarnerata kingorna Kalaallit Nunaaliaq-
82
[KAL] Eqqumiitsulianit
pisiarineqartunit Gitz-Johansenip
titartaariaasianik nalinginnaasumik
takutitsipput.
[DK] De indkøbte værker er typiske
eksempler på Gitz-Johansens streg.
[GB] The acquired works are typical
examples of Gitz-Johansen’s style.
qissimanngilaq, taamaattumillu qalipagaq inuiaqatigiit oqalut-
tuarisaanerat eqqarsaatigalugu aamma eqqumiitsuliaalluni
pingaaruteqartoq. Tassani isiginnittaatsit assigiinngitsut immin-
nullu assortuuttut Kalaallit Nunaata nutarteriffigineqarnera-
nut atatillugu atuuttut takutinneqarput, Nuuk Kunstmuseum
pisiarineqartut pillugit tusagassiuutitigut nalunaarummi allappoq.
Gitz-Johansen eqqumiitsuliortuunermi Kalaallit Nunaannullu
angalasartuunermi saniatigut piffissap ilaani misigisassarsioru-
matuut peqatigiiffiannut, Eventyrernes Klubimut, aamma siulit-
taasuusimavoq.
(Najoqqutaq: Nuuk Kunstmuseum)
Suluk nr. 1
Inflight Magazine 2020Et imponerende 5-stjernet konferencecenter
Hvilken udsigt kunne du tænke dig
fra dit konferencelokale?
Udsigt til ægte verdensarv i konstant forandring
Hotel Arctic ligger ud til Ilulissat Isfjord, der er på UNESCOs
verdensarvliste. Her fås udsigten næppe bedre.
Oplev det, mange drømmer om, men aldrig når at prøve
Som konferencedeltager på Hotel Arctic er fritiden mere vild
og eventyrlig end normalt. Oplevelser af en helt anden verden
- sætter tingene i det rette perspektiv.
BO O K DIN KONFER ENC E ONLI NE NU
Adr. Boks 1501
3952 Ilulissat
Grønland
H OTELA RC T I C .C OM[KAL] J.E.C. Rasmussen – Nuuk
Kunstmuseumimi qalipagaq alla.
[DK] J.E.C. Rasmussen – et andet
maleri på Nuuk Kunstmuseum.
[GB] J.E.C. Rasmussen – another
painting at Nuuk Art Museum.
[KAL] Eqqumiitsulianut katersugaasivik
Ny Carlsbergfondimit perngaammik
tunissuteqarfigineqarpoq.
[DK] Det er første gang, at kunstmuseet
får støtte fra Ny Carlsbergfondet.
[GB] It is the first time that the art museum
has received support from the New
Carlsberg Foundation.
En sanselig maler
Et stykke grønlandsk
kunsthistorie er kommet hjem
En drøm er gået i opfyldelse for Nuuk Kunstmu-
seum ved købet af fire Gitz-Johansen-værker til
samlingen. Nyerhvervelsen sker via en donation
fra Ny Carlsbergfondet. Der er tale om tre vær-
ker på papir og et oliemaleri.
– De fire værker viser Gitz-Johansens karak-
teristiske legende, lette og helt enkle streger og
hans sanselige blik på den grønlandske kultur,
forklarer museumsleder Nivi Christensen.
– Værkerne skal være med til at vise, hvor forskelligt de dansk-udsendte
kunstnere så Grønland. Emanuel A. Petersen, Jette Bang og Gitz-Johansen
befandt sig alle sammen i Grønland i årene omkring 1930. Petersen foku-
serede på naturen, og mennesket har kun en meget lille rolle i hans værker.
De er domineret af farvestrålende solnedgange og rejser på hundeslæde
over det smukke landskab. Hans værker er næsten altid malet med store
afstande og enorme vidder. Gitz-Johansen viste kulturen og fokuserede på
kvinderne og mønstrene tæt på og sanseligt, uddyber Nivi Christensen.
84
Eskimoen dør
Ifølge museumslederen giver de fire værker – og nogle af museets øvrige,
udenlandske værker fra perioden – et indblik i den måde, hvorpå Grønland
blev opfattet under kolonitiden. Set udefra.
– Det store oliemaleri med titlen »Eskimoen dør« er en direkte kom-
mentar fra Gitz-Johansen til den udvikling, der blev igangsat i Grønland
med G50 og G60. Han udtrykte ofte sin utilfredshed med moderniserin-
gen af Grønland, som i hans øjne var en ødelæggelse af den eskimoiske
kultur. Han satte ikke sine fødder i Grønland igen efter moderniseringen
blev igangsat, og maleriet er derfor også et vigtigt samfundshistorisk
værk. Det viser de forskellige og modsatrettede opfattelser, der herskede
i forhold til moderniseringen af Grønland, skriver Nuuk Kunstmuseum i en
pressemeddelelse om indkøbene.
Ud over at være kunstner og grønlandsfarer var Gitz-Johansen i en pe-
riode også formand for Eventyrernes Klub. (Kilde: Nuuk Kunstmuseum) 
Suluk nr. 1
Inflight Magazine 2020Peqataagit, siunissap ilusilerniarnerani
Polar Seafood ilinniagaqarnissamik taamallu
Kalaallit Nunaanni inuussutissarsiutit
pingaarnersaannut atatillugu suliffinnik
pilersitsiortornissamut pingaartitsisuuvoq,
tulluusimaarluta aalisakkanik, raajanik
saattussanillu pitsaanerpaanik pilersuisin-
naaniassagatta.
Help to shape the future
Polar Seafood takes pride in training people
and creating jobs in Greenland’s most
important industry, so that we can proudly
continue to deliver the finest quality seafood.
A strong brand worldwide
HOTEL Sømandshjemmene
- Mere end bare et hotel!
www.soemandshjem.gl
NUUK - SISIMIUT - AASIAAT[KAL] [DK] [GB] Gitz-Johansen.
A sensual painter
A piece of historic Greenlandic
art has come home
A dream has come true for Nuuk Museum of
Art after the acquisition of four Gitz-Johans-
en works for its collection. The new purchas-
es were made possible by a donation from
the New Carlsberg Foundation. There are
three works on paper and one oil painting.
– The four works show Gitz-Johansen’s
characteristically playful, light and very
simple strokes and his sensual view of
Greenland’s culture, explains curator Nivi Christensen.
– These works help to show how diff erent the artists sent out by
Denmark saw Greenland. Emanuel A. Petersen, Jette Bang and Gitz-
Johansen were all in Greenland in the years around 1930. Petersen
focused on nature and people play only a very small role in his works.
They are dominated by colourful sunsets and dog-sleds travelling
across the beautiful landscape. His works almost always show great
distances and vast expanses. Gitz-Johansen showed culture and fo-
cused on the women and the patterns up close in a sensual manner,
explains Nivi Christensen.
“He often expressed his dissatisfaction
with the modernisation of Greenland,
which in his view meant the destruction
of the Eskimo culture”
86
[KAL] Gitz-Johansenip eqqumiitsuliai
alutornarluartuullutillu misikkarissupput.
[DK] Gitz-Johansens kunst er koloristisk og sanselig.
[GB] Gitz-Johansen’s art is coloristic and sensual.
Suluk nr. 1
Infl ight Magazine 2020
The Eskimo dies
According to the curator, the four works – and some of the museum’s
other foreign works from the period – provide an insight into how
Greenland was perceived during colonial times, from the outside
looking in.
– The big oil painting entitled ”The Eskimo dies” is a direct com-
ment from Gitz-Johansen on the development that started in Green-
land with G50 and G60. He often expressed his dissatisfaction with
the modernisation of Greenland, which in his view meant the de-
struction of the Eskimo culture. After the start of modernisation,
he did not set foot in Greenland again and the painting is therefore
also an important socio-historic work. It illustrates the diff erent and
opposing views that were prevalent regarding the modernisation of
Greenland, according to the Nuuk Museum of Art in a press release
regarding the acquisitions.
In addition to being an artist and explorer of Greenland, Gitz-
Johansen was also chairman of the Adventurer’s Club for a while.
(Source: Nuuk Museum of Art)
― Nuuk Museum of ArtKalaallit Nunaat – suliffissaqqissoq
Grønland – en fantastisk arbejdsplads
Suliffissarsiortarfik
nutaarsiassanullu nittartagaq
2018-imi 1,2 millionit atuisimapput
– Danmarkimit 400.000-t sinnerlugit
JOB.Sermitsiaq.AG
jobsite og nyhedshjemmeside
Over 1,2 millioner brugere i 2018
– over 400.000 brugere fra DKInnisaq
Innisaq timmisartup, napparsimasunut angallas-
sinermini inuunermik annaassisarneranut, nunallu
inuinut annertuumik pingaaruteqar neranut
ersiutaavoq.
Oqaluttualiami Innersuarnik taaguutilimmi,
inunnillu uummarsaaqqittarnermik imaqartumi,
Innisamut tunngaviupput anersaat ikiortaasartut.
Innisaq toqqaannaq nutserlugu isumaqarpoq
inuunermik tunniussisoq.
Innisaq aamma oqaatsimit innersuussamit, tassa
nakorsamut innersuussinermit, tunngaveqarpoq.
Titartagaq Innersuarnut tunngasoq Christian
Fleischer Rex-ip sanaaraa.
Innisaq
Innisaq hentyder til fl yets store betydning for
landets befolkning, når det er ude at redde liv som
ambulancefl y.
Innisaq stammer fra myten om ildvæsnerne In-
nersuit, der var en slags hjælpeånder, som kunne
bringe folk tilbage til livet.
Direkte oversat betyder Innisaq: den som man
har givet liv. Innisaq kommer desuden af beteg-
nelsen innersuussaq, som betyder én der bliver
henvist til en læge.
Christian Fleischer Rex har lavet illustrationen,
der viser ildvæsnerne Innersuit.
Innisaq
Innisaq refers to the great importance of the
aircraft to the people of the country, when it is out
saving lives as an air ambulance.
Innisaq comes from the myth about the Innersuit;
fi re creatures which were spirit helpers that could
bring people back to life.
Directly translated, Innisaq means: that which has
given life. Innisaq is also derived from the term
“innersuussaq” which means one who has been
referred to a doctor.
Christian Fleischer Rex has made an illustration
showing the Innersuit fi re creatures.
86
Suluk nr. 1
